docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay, Jan. 29 (Associated Press).--Sir Ernest Shackleton, the British explorer, died Jan. 5 on board the steamship Quest, on which he was making another expedition into the antarctic regions. Death was due to angina pectoris and occurred when the Quest was off the Gritvicken Station.
